CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 11, 1970, pg. 24, reads: "Model Cities Elections - the following areas have nominated these Candidates for Chairmanship and Vice-Chairmanship of their respective neighborhood planning teams...Jeannette Webb, Melvin Jackson. Not shown, but in running - Edward Hines, Samuel Lawler, Charles Baker...Area IV, Wednesday, July 15, 1970, 7:30 P.M., Place: Bethel AME Church, 2720 Webster Avenue, Pittsburgh, Pa. 15219"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of two women wearing light colored outfits, including Jeannette Webb, and two men wearing suits, including Melvin Jackson, standing outside of New Pittsburgh Courier building, with newspaper in window with headline "National Drive To Halt Construction...", 315 Carson Street, South Side
